I don't believe that Unreliables would work here since there is the clause:
catch (NoDriverFoundException e) {
                    // we explicitly want this exception to fail fast without retries
                    throw e;
}

and Unreliables waits until a timeout is reached no matter what. Don't have time now to check, but probably using Unreliables might make it only more complicated.

